      "name": "Synthesized prior literature basis for FEA modeling assumptions",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies — including published finite element analyses of spinal instrumentation, cadaveric biomechanical datasets, and regulatory precedent from analogous 510(k) submissions — that collectively establish the theoretical and empirical foundation for the modeling assumptions employed in this COU. The synthesis integrates findings from at least seven peer-reviewed publications spanning 2008–2021, covering material characterization, contact modeling best practices, and mesh convergence criteria for metallic spinal implant FEA. The depth and breadth of this evidence base is considered sufficient to anchor the claim provenance without further upstream decomposition."
